Due to the ongoing poor air quality in the region, 509J school buildings will remain closed Monday, September 14th.

The school meal program will operate, but only at the school locations listed below:
Madras High School: 7:30 AM - 8:30 AM
Bridges High School: 7:30 AM - 8:30 AM
Warm Springs K-8 Academy: 7:30 AM - 8:30 AM
Bus stop deliveries will not occur.

All virtual classes will continue as scheduled.

If conditions require the building closure to continue beyond Monday, we will provide updates through the usual district communications channels.

Thank you

Children need good nutrition all year long. When school is out during the summer months, many children no longer have access to even one nutritious meal each day. The Summer Food Service Program helps to fill the gap. To find a site, call 2-1-1, text “Food” or “Comida” to 877-877, or visit Summer Food Oregon.

If you have questions, please contact ODE Child Nutrition Programs - Community Nutrition, at (503) 947-5894 or ode.communitynutrition@ode.state.or.us.

In addition, our own 509J Summer Meals Program provides free breakfast and lunch to any child 18 years and younger. Child must present to receive meals. Summer Meals Served July 1 – August 31, 2020, served Monday – Friday CLOSED JULY 3, 2020. See our website for locations: https://bit.ly/3dMErgc

post_text:
509J Will Reopen Schools in the Fall

Jefferson County School District 509J and other school districts in Oregon received guidance yesterday from the Oregon Department of Education for reopening schools next fall. The District is already developing the first in a series of surveys for family members to complete to help inform the plan for opening schools on September 8, 2020. Families should plan to receive the first survey next week or they can access the survey on the District website.

District and school leaders have been planning for the last few weeks for safety and cleaning precautions which will be put in place for students and staff. 509J will continue to collaborate with the Jefferson County Health Department in order to open schools while continuing to follow health protocols. District leadership is confident that students will be able to return to classrooms and will develop additional options for some students.

shared_text:
Madras High School ASB & Activities
April 8 at 9:40 AM ·

Last night was the first in the Oregon Be the Light Movement.

Stadium lights across the state are coming on to show support and hope for all students. Schools across the state like Madras, Ontario, Phoenix, Bend, Mt. View, Culver, Corvallis are all participating in support of their students. More schools will be joining with some participating nightly and others participating on just Friday nights throughout the school year. Lights are on one minute for each day of school missed during this pandemic.

The stadium lights at Madras' Stampede Stadium came on at 20:20 hours (military time) in honor of our 2020 graduating class. This class will have endured and prospered in ways that have not been experienced in a lifetime.

Here at Madras High School we want to say thank you to all of our students and especially our student-athletes who have to date not had a spring sports season.

If you see the stadium lights on you will know that we miss the "Friday Night Lights" and look forward to seeing our students again.

509J is proud to announce the launch of our Supplemental Learning Resources site, to share resources and guidance to supplement learning at home. Resources will be available
• on our site at https://sites.google.com/509j.net/remotelearning/
• at all Grab and Go Meal Sites
• at our School District Office lobby (open 8 – 3, Monday – Friday). Available materials include hard copies of website materials, and books for all ages.

We hope that families can partner with children every day to read, write, speak, do math, get some exercise, and help one another. A schedule is nice, but remember to be flexible and have fun! If you are having difficulty accessing content, need assistance, or have questions, email RemoteLearning@509j.net or call 541-475-7743 to leave us a message.

February 5 at 7:53 PM ·

MADRAS FOOTBALL STAR SIGNS LETTER OF INTENT WITH PORTLAND STATE

Today was national signing day for Division I football.

High school athletes from across the country signed their letters of intent to play football at the next level and one such athlete is a familiar face to our viewers.

Treyvon Easterling, a running back from Madras High School, was one of the stars of our series last fall “Why Madras.” Today, he signed on the dotted line and said “he’s never been happier.”

Central Oregon Daily’s Eric Lindstrom was there for the ceremony at the school and talked to Easterling about his future in the sport.

shared_text:
Central Oregon Daily News
January 16 at 7:25 PM ·

Bend ultrarunner Mario Mendoza Jr. set a new world record for running a 50K on a treadmill.

The decorated runner made the attempt at Madras High School where he works as an assistant track coach and works with youth in the community.

Mendoza finished the 31 miles in 2:59:03, smashing the old record by 46 seconds.

This is the inspiring story behind Mendoza and the record attempt.

Central Oregon Daily's Eric Lindstrom tells the story.

January 16 at 7:25 PM ·

Bend ultrarunner Mario Mendoza Jr. set a new world record for running a 50K on a treadmill.

The decorated runner made the attempt at Madras High School where he works as an assistant track coach and works with youth in the community.

Mendoza finished the 31 miles in 2:59:03, smashing the old record by 46 seconds.

This is the inspiring story behind Mendoza and the record attempt.

Central Oregon Daily's Eric Lindstrom tells the story.

The Early Learning Hub of Central Oregon is currently enrolling kids in the UPSTART program, this is an online early literacy program.
--In only 20 minutes per day, 5 days a week, UPSTART helps support your child's reading development.
--The program is free to families.
--A Chromebook computer, headphones, and a mouse are provided (you get to keep upon completion of the program).
--If you do not have internet access, the Early Learning Hub can provide internet for the time you are in the program.

Families can enroll here: bit.ly/ELHub_UPSTART

Orientation visits are starting soon and spots are limited!

If you have questions please reach out to Shelley Irwin: shelley.irwin@hdesd.org 541-693-5678

From our Band/Choir director Jared McFarlin:

Greetings all,
I want to let you know about an upcoming event on Thursday, November 7. The Music Department will be presenting a concert in honor of our veterans. Please share at will and invite any veterans you might have connections with to attend. There is a suggested donation of $10 or three canned food items, but of course all are welcome to attend with or without the donation. Funds will be donated to Central Oregon Veterans Ranch, and food will be donated for baskets created by Jefferson County VSO.
Thanks for sharing!
Jared

We did find one familiar face at today's signing day, kicker Keagan Prevett, whose inspirational story we've been following the past year, was there committing to his post-high school plans.

DEADLINE IS TODAY: The JCSD 509-J Board of Directors has two Positions Openings for Board of Directors: Position #4 / Position #5
Note: Both Positions will start July 1, 2019 and are 4 year positions. This election will be conducted by mail.

If you are interested in running for Position #4 or Position #5 in the May 21, 2019 Special Election:

Each candidate for the position listed above must file a declaration of candidacy or petition for nomination for office with the Elections Department of Jefferson County, Oregon, no later than the 61st day before the date of the regular district election. The filing deadline is 5:00pm on March 21, 2019. Filing forms are available at the Jefferson County Clerk’s Office, 66 SE D Street, Suite C, Madras, OR 97741, on the Jefferson County website (www.co.jefferson.or.us) or the Secretary of State’s website: http://sos.oregon.gov/elections/documents/SEL190.pdf.

If you have additional questions, please contact Board Secretary Tessa Bailey at 541-475-6192



DEADLINE is 5:00 PM on March 21, 2019

post_text:
A message from Superintendent Ken Parshall:
Dear parents and community members;
While conditions on main roads and in the cities of Madras, Metolius, and Warm Springs were very passable today, we were still forced to close school. Snow drifts of 1.5 to 2 feet covered some roads in rural areas of the district. In addition, there were some rural roads on which freezing rain had fallen. It is frustrating to lose a day of education for our students, but we must consider the safe passage of rural areas of our county as well as the conditions within the cities. Thank you for your understanding.

Sincerely,
Ken Parshall

AGAINST ALL ODDS

Madras Teenager Overcomes Condition to Become Kicker for Football Team

If you watch 17-year-old Kaegan Prevett kick field goals for the Madras High School football team, you would never know that he has been battling a condition called Treacher Collins Syndrome since he was born.

Central Oregon Daily's Eric Lindstrom spoke with Kaegan, his parents and his coach to hear more of his inspiring story.

Central Oregon Daily News
May 8, 2018 at 6:54 PM ·

SIGNING DAY

High School Coach Creates His Own Signing Day for Incoming Freshmen

A local high school coach is tearing a page right out of the college playbook to generate excitement in his school's football program.

Central Oregon Daily's Eric Lindstrom heads to Madras and Warm Springs K-8 Academy for a new “Signing Day” event designed for middle school football players.

Madras High School football coach Kurt Taylor says his problem is not unique, and that’s because of the overall decline in young boys playing football. Every high school coach has to find new ways to get kids excited about their football programs.

post_text: Way to go Alex!😊
shared_text:
MHS Physical Education
May 5, 2018 at 5:09 PM ·

Special moment for Coach Taylor and myself... The 2018 “Turnaround Student of the Year” was Alex Hernandez. This kid has come a long way. Alex represents many kids coming in to high school. Negative attitude regarding academics and no clear goals for his future. He began changing near the end of his sophomore year. Started talking with teachers, counselors and other school staff about what it would take to get caught up enough to start playing football. He mapped it out, chipped away and by fall of his junior year, Alex was playing varsity football and had all A’s and B’s... This is a true turnaround story. And it can be any of our students. You might not start out strong but look inside and find your personal motivation and start setting goals. You can change your future. Alex went from not caring about school or academics, to playing football and is now planning on attending PCC next fall to work toward his automotive/mechanics degree. Very proud teacher here! Congrats Alex. We wish you the best!!!

We are selling 5 VIP tables at each of the BBX and GBX playoff games tomorrow and next Friday!!

Tables are $40/table and seat 4 people (only $10/person). The VIP section is located in the upper gym, above the south-side bleachers. The 5 VIP tables include: 4 tickets for the gate fee, 4 nicely cushioned chairs, 4 VIP passes for access to the upper gym, upper gym rest room access, as well as 4 free water bottles and snacks. This promotion is a first come, first serve basis. Please contact Coach McConnell ASAP to reserve your table. You will pick up your passes in the gym lobby prior to the start of the games.

BBX vs. Tillamook on Sat. 2/24 @ 5pm.
GBX vs. TBA on Fri. 3/2 @ TBA.

Email McConnell at smcconnell@509j.net or Facebook message her on on her personal, SB or Activities page.

Do you know an exceptional teacher? Nominate them for the Oregon Teacher of the Year! http://oregonteacheroftheyear.org/#nominations

Candidates for Oregon Teacher of the Year should be exceptionally dedicated, knowledgeable, and skilled educators in grades preK-12.

In addition, candidates for Oregon Teacher of the Year should:

* Be an expert in their field who guides students of all backgrounds and abilities to achieve excellence.
* Collaborate with colleagues, students, and families to create a school culture of respect and success.
* Deliberately connect the classroom and key stakeholders to foster a strong community at large.
* Demonstrate leadership and innovation in and outside of the classroom walls that embodies lifelong learning.
* Express themselves in an engaging and articulate way.

post_text: Congratulations Jazelle Fernandez and Nichole Skeels from Buff Elementary and Kannon Whiting from Madras Elementary! These students competed in the 26th annual Inventerprise contest, a science problem-solving contest sponsored by Bend Research. Nearly 1,600 students from 41 Central Oregon schools participated in this year’s contest. Judges reviewed approximately 1,150 entries – another record year – and announced the winners today!

Information includes the state’s official notice and opt-out form. Please contact your school principal if you have questions about the opt-out process, or about state tests given in our school.

shared_text:
KTVZ - NewsChannel 21
November 6, 2017 at 2:38 PM ·

From the Joint Hometown News Service : U.S. Air Force Airman 1st Class Benjamin M. Ellis graduated from basic military training at Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland, San Antonio, Texas.

The airman completed an intensive, eight-week program that included training in military discipline and studies, Air Force core values, physical fitness, and basic warfare principles and skills.

Airmen who complete basic training also earn four credits toward an associate in applied science degree through the Community College of the Air Force.

Ellis is the son of Tobias B. and Connie M. Ellis of Madras, Ore.

He is a 2017 graduate of Madras High School, Madras, Ore.
